<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-12-14T04:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-12-14T04:16:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">371.1113Keller, W. N.: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-14T11:00:00+01:44"><hi rend="italic">December 14,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>58. Department’s telegram No. 42, December 13, 6 p.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d648fn15">Not printed.</note> Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            has withdrawn objection to giving publicity to the fact that the
                            Rumanian Government will compensate Keller. Case is settled except
                            determination amount of claim.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>